criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  circulatory and respiratory stability;

          -  readiness for oral feeding according to each child's Speech-Language Pathologist
             assessment;

          -  prematurely born infants who will be in the process of transfer from enteral nutrition
             to full oral feeding and will be fed orally at least 4 times within twenty-four hours;

          -  researcher must be a right handed person (right hand is the dominant hand);

          -  each infant will be fed with one kind of bottle and nipple;

          -  parents will give a informed consent to participate their infant in the study.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  disorders which could significantly affect the feeding course, such as cleft lip
             and/or palate, facial paralysis and/or congenital defects of the facial skeleton;

          -  the presence of detected congenital abnormalities and metabolic diseases;

          -  newborns after abdomen chirurgical treatment;

          -  low Apgar score (less than 5 points at the 5th and 10th minute of the measurement);

          -  administered analgesics, anticonvulsants and sedatives <72 hours from extubation prior
             the trial;

          -  parenterally fed infants;

          -  infants with administered intravenous infusion with glucose;

          -  parents refusal to participate in the study or when bottle-feeding will not be the
             parental preference.
